  %body
    %h1
      CSS Validator Binary Distribution
    %p
      This a binary distribution of
      %a{ :href => "http://jigsaw.w3.org/css-validator" }
        W3C CSS Validator
      \.
      It was built from the
      %a{ :href => "http://dev.w3.org/cvsweb/2002/css-validator" }
        source
      on June 25, 2006.
      No modifications were made.
    %p
      This distribution is provided
      %a{ :href => "#asis" }
        as is
      to make testing a large number of CSS files easier.
    %h2
      Requirements
    %p
      A Java 2 Virtual Machine is required to use the validator.
      You can download one from
      %a{ :href => "http://java.sun.com/" }
        Sun
      if you do not have one installed.
    %h2
      Usage
    %h2
      Summary
    %p
      %code
        java -jar
        %samp
          \~/css-validator/
        css-validator.jar [-options] files URLs
    %h2
      Sample
    %pre
      java -jar ~/css-validator/css-validator.jar f1.css http://illumit.com/
    %h2
      Options
    %dl
      %dt
        \-e
      %dd
        Show errors only.
      %dt
        \-html
      %dd
        Output HTML.
      %dt
        \-css1 | -css2 | -css21 | -css3 | -svg | -svgbasic | -svgtiny
      %dd
        Specify CSS version. CSS2 is the default.
    %h2
      Support
    %p
      If you have questions about how this distribution is built or packaged,
      %a{ :href => "mailto:contact@illumit.com" }
        mailto:contact@illumit.com
      \.
    %p
      Use the CSS Validator
      %a{ :href => "http://jigsaw.w3.org/css-validator/Email" }
        Feedback
      page if you have any questions or problems with the validator itself.
    %p.Footnote
      Updates are announced on via
      %a.RSSLink{ :href => "http://www.illumit.com/site.rss", :rel => "alternate", :type => "application/rss+xml" }
        RSS
    /
